OL,3,C'We were cheaper than chimps' -
OL,4,CCampaigners call for justice over
OL,5,Cinfected blood
OL,7,FLike thousands of other patients he
OL,8,Fwas given a clotting agent called
OL,9,FFactor VIII, a revolutionary treatment
OL,10,Fthat negated the need for lengthy
OL,11,Fblood transfusions.
OL,13,FBut it was made from pooled plasma,
OL,14,Fobtained from high-risk donors such as
OL,15,Fprison in-mates and drug users in
OL,16,FAmerica, and it brought catastrophic
OL,17,Fresults.
OL,19,FIn all, 7,500 haemophiliacs were
OL,20,Finfected with HIV or Hepatitis in the
OL,21,F1970s and 80s.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/15
